The Estonian 500 Krooni bill (500 EEK) is a denomination of the Estonian currency .
Carl Robert Jakobson, who was an Estonian politician, publisher, writer and promoter of agriculture (1841-1882), is featured on the front side of the bill, which is why the 500 Krooni bill is often called a "Jakobson".
A barn swallow in flight on a landscape background is featured on the reverse side of the bill.
